6. Implementation Spotlight: The OpenClaw Pattern

Production-grade agents use a "Search then Get" architecture to keep the context window lean and prevent the "RAM" from overflowing with irrelevant data.

The Workflow Sequence:

1. MemorySearch: The agent runs a hybrid search and receives a 700-character snippet—a lean preview used to judge relevance without bloating the prompt.
2. Citation Check: The agent identifies the "source of truth" using citation metadata provided in the snippet.
3. MemoryGet: Only after confirming relevance does the agent use a specific tool to pull the exact line range of the text needed.

// Tool Definition for MemoryGet:
{
  "tool": "MemoryGet",
  "parameters": {
    "path": "memory/2026-02-10.md",
    "startLine": 142,
    "lineCount": 20
  },
  "description": "Retrieves the full text of a specific memory after a search confirms its relevance."
}



