7. Summary Checklist for Learners

* [ ] Context is a Budget: Agents don't "remember" everything at once; they fetch information "Just-in-Time" to save on costs and prevent model distraction.
* [ ] Hybrid is Non-Negotiable: Successful agents require both a compass (Semantic) to find the neighborhood and a street address (Keyword) to find the specific door.
* [ ] Memory is an Action, Not a Database: High-quality memory involves active management—extracting facts, consolidating updates, and deleting contradictions.

Final Concept: Just-in-Time Verification The most advanced agents, like GitHub Copilot, employ Just-in-Time (JIT) Verification. Because code and facts change, the agent doesn't just trust a stored memory. Instead, it checks the citations in real-time against the current branch of the codebase. If the code has changed since the memory was recorded, the agent "self-heals" by ignoring the stale data and updating its memory to reflect the new reality.
